        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 10:13PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 1013 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chesterhill, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bartlett and Fleming.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
